{
  "stem": "7177.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember that I was supposed to sit on little chairs and make sure that my pleated skirt was all over the place and not over-- you know, above my knees, and all kinds of little things.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you make, make a [GERMAN], I think that's what the Germans call it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you would kind of kneel down a tiny little bit if your mother would introduce you to somebody.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Good morning, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Such-and-So, and that kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was terribly important.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Good manners were terribly important.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It helped me a great deal later in my life, because I was born in such a small town.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when you later on go over the whole world, if you have good manners or if you have at least some manners, you get along anyplace.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It doesn't really matter.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One of the funny things I wanted to tell you, my job during Yom Tov was the day before-- because I'm thinking of it now, because next week is Yom Kippur, the-- my job before Yom Kippur was I had to tear the toilet paper, because we could not tear toilet paper on Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's unheard of, right?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then-- so those were the beautiful little things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then Pesach Seder, my father, of course, who spoke-- who could read, you know, Hebrew very, very well-- and we, of course, learned it also.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we went to Hebrew school on Sundays and so on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he could pronounce it and read it faster than we did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of the games for Seder was who could sing [HEBREW] the quickest.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my father always won.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that-- those were the things that we did at home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My mother was very precise, very exact.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Her standard saying was [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
